Rating: 4
This was an excellent recipe! I customized my stuffing for a gluten-free, vegetarian version: about 1 cup of cooked wild rice blend, some caramelized shallots, about 3/4 cup shredded young kale leaves, 2 cloves garlic, 1/4 cup chopped walnuts, 1/2 chopped apple, chopped herbs (4 sage leaves and a sprig of rosemary plus three pinches freshly dried thyme). I used half Gruyere and half seaside smoked cheddar from Whole Foods. My carnival squash was stuffed too full to accommodate the cap, so I cooked it in a Le Creuset bell pepper-shaped iron casserole with the lid on for all but the last 20 minutes of cooking. One of the BEST dishes I've ever eaten. Perfect meatless Thanksgiving entree.

