Despite my initial sense of this being an odd recipe, it really was so good. I had a large Long Island Cheese pumpkin that I wanted to use so I made extra filling using the following additions/substitutions: I used whole wheat baguette, left out the bacon (sounded heavy and I wanted to go veggie), and included a bunch of mustard greens. I used scallions, no chives or thyme, fresh nutmeg. I loved the addition of the greens which cut the richness of the cream to some extent. Both my husband (a major bacon lover) and I felt the absence of bacon was a good thing because this is not a light dish. I would definitely make this again and agree with other reviewers that there are so many ways you could play around with the filling. I just had leftovers which were delish!

