Rating: 3
This has some real possibilities; I love the concept. Mine turned out pretty good but would need some tinkering to be great--a little bland so definitely more herbs, maybe some cooked spinach. I'd say the adventurous cook who is willing to experiment and possibly flop could be well-rewarded here. I used the cooked rice/cooked bulk Italian sausage variation (about 1 cup rice, 1/2 lb. sausage) and baked in individual 1 1/2 lb. pumpkins for about 90 minutes. Served with a salad of mixed greens with pomegranate seeds, goat cheese, and the pumpkin seeds I'd scooped out and toasted in the oven. Made an apple/almond paste galette with whipped cream for dessert and it was an interesting fall meal. Looking forward to experimenting further and trying the original bread recipe.

